      "skills": "Students will be able to: (a) rearrange a quadratic equation into the standard form ax squared plus bx plus c equals zero; (b) factorise the left-hand side into two linear factors; (c) set each factor equal to zero and solve for the variable; (d) evaluate both solutions against the real-world context and justify the accepted answer.",
      "attitudes": "Students will appreciate that mathematics produces multiple answers and that critical thinking about context is as important as computational accuracy.",
